# fusion-box wine patch 0001
# Adds server-side decoration (xdg-decoration-unstable-v1) support to
# winewayland.drv so that KDE Plasma's KWin no longer paints SSD borders
# unilaterally - wine now owns the decoration negotiation and reports the
# correct content geometry, fixing window drag + click-through to widgets.
#
# Source: wine merge request !10259 (still in flight against wine master
# as of wine 11.10 / 2026-06-06), https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/wine/-/merge_requests/10259
# Authors: see the MR commits - we did not write the protocol-level work.
#
# Diff regenerated locally against wine-11.10 source to capture two
# additional hunks in dlls/winewayland.drv/waylanddrv.h that were needed
# because waylanddrv.h drifted between MR-author-time and 11.10 (the
# pointer-warp protocol header was added in between). Both fixes are
# trivial: one extra #include line, one extra struct field. No semantic
# changes vs. the upstream MR.
#
# Apply from the wine source root: `patch -p1 < this-file`
#
